commits.author: Jungwoo Song
commits.message:
Valkey connector (#1743)

* feat: Add dependency for valkey-glide

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Add Valkey adapter

- Using same url prefix(valkey://) supporting standalone and cluster mode
- Use query param for checking mode.
- Standalone mode supports selecting database and cluster mode doesn't support it (but after Valkey 9, it can support database mode)

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Valkey Connector

- Implement valkey connector based on redis connector but using other library, Valkey-GLIDE managed by Valkey organization.
- Use mget and pipeline put at standalone and cluster mode
- Use Hash slot for reducing network latency at cluster mode.
- When tested with 10 keys, Valkey connector is 5 ~ 20% faster at standalone mode and up to 70%(avg 60%+) faster at cluster mode.

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* test: add test for valkey connector

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: add specific version for supporting pipelinig

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: linting

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: add checking memory equality at test

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Use extra config for simple paramters

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: remove valkey-glide depedency from common.txt

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Add try-except and prevent memory leak

- Add try-except under assert statement for checking error
- Add memory_obj.ref_count_down() for preventing memory leak

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: double check for config and extra_config

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: lint

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* docs: Add docs for valkey connector

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: Move import statement to the head of file and exception handling

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

commits.author: Jungwoo Song
commits.message:
Valkey connector (#1743)

* feat: Add dependency for valkey-glide

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Add Valkey adapter

- Using same url prefix(valkey://) supporting standalone and cluster mode
- Use query param for checking mode.
- Standalone mode supports selecting database and cluster mode doesn't support it (but after Valkey 9, it can support database mode)

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Valkey Connector

- Implement valkey connector based on redis connector but using other library, Valkey-GLIDE managed by Valkey organization.
- Use mget and pipeline put at standalone and cluster mode
- Use Hash slot for reducing network latency at cluster mode.
- When tested with 10 keys, Valkey connector is 5 ~ 20% faster at standalone mode and up to 70%(avg 60%+) faster at cluster mode.

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* test: add test for valkey connector

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: add specific version for supporting pipelinig

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: linting

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: add checking memory equality at test

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Use extra config for simple paramters

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: remove valkey-glide depedency from common.txt

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: Add try-except and prevent memory leak

- Add try-except under assert statement for checking error
- Add memory_obj.ref_count_down() for preventing memory leak

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* feat: double check for config and extra_config

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: lint

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* docs: Add docs for valkey connector

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>

* fix: Move import statement to the head of file and exception handling

Signed-off-by: Jungwoo Song <bluayer@gmail.com>
